Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a cellular edge caching design in an ultra-dense network, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a novel caching algorithm that incorporates temporal dynamics of content popularity and storage constraints, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper uses mean-field game theory to develop the caching algorithm, which falls under the scope of game theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control of caching in a network, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with caching of multimedia content in a network, which falls under the scope of multimedia.
